        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Leicester were very good and Man City were poor. I disagree that money doesn't win you titles, it did for City... and Chelsea.... and PSG and pretty much every major team in Europe at some point (although I have no problem with teams having large financial resources off the back of being successful since the success came first) but if you have a whole squad on the same page, then paper worth can be nulled somewhat. With still a 3rd of the season left to go, I doubt Leicester will win the title or even be a contender come the nitty-gritty. Sometimes inexperience can be helpful if the only experience is that of losing, but we've seen better teams than Leicester flop from better positions. Once they go from "unlikely winners" to "probable winners", we'll see whether they have it in them. It's relatively simple to play when there's no pressure, not so when people expect you to win. It's more than merely a case of hanging on, as history has shown. Top 4 is a probability now though.

          @MSNism- Money can/does win you titles- Chelsea, Man City, PSG are only where they are because they were taken over by immensely rich people who poured triple-figured millions into their clubs. I'm not saying Leicester 100% wont win the title but it's more than a case of hanging on for 13 games.
